line_1: Jerusalem a prey, her glory soil'd,
line_2: Her princes captive, and her treasures spoil'd;

line_1: And thus his grand designs were soil'd –
line_2: By death were spoilers ever spoil'd.

line_1: And shining silks with greasy powder soil'd?
line_2: So shall their partners mourn their laces spoil'd,

line_1: Twa vet'rans grown gray, wi' their muskets sair soil'd,
line_2: Wi' a sigh were relating how hard they had toil'd;
